#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:73
#, no-wrap
msgid "The Ansible vocabulary"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:84
#, no-wrap
msgid "The **management machine**: the machine on which Ansible is installed. Since Ansible is **agentless**, no software is deployed on the managed servers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:84
#, no-wrap
msgid "The **inventory**: a file containing information about the managed servers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:84
#, no-wrap
msgid "The **tasks**: a task is a block defining a procedure to be executed (e.g., create a user or a group, install a software package, etc.).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:84
#, no-wrap
msgid "A **module**: a module abstracts a task. There are many modules provided by Ansible.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:84
#, no-wrap
msgid "The **playbooks**: a simple file in yaml format defining the target servers and the tasks to be performed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:84
#, no-wrap
msgid "A **role**: a role allows you to organize the playbooks and all the other necessary files (templates, scripts, etc.) to facilitate the sharing and reuse of code.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:84
#, no-wrap
msgid "A **collection**: a collection includes a logical set of playbooks, roles, modules, and plugins.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:84
#, no-wrap
msgid "The **facts**: these are global variables containing information about the system (machine name, system version, network interface and configuration, etc.).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:84
#, no-wrap
msgid "The **handlers**: these are used to cause a service to be stopped or restarted in the event of a change.\n"
msgstr ""

