#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:659
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example of Apache and MySQL playbook"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:662
#, no-wrap
msgid "The following playbook allows us to install Apache and MariaDB on our target servers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:664
#, no-wrap
msgid "Create a `test.yml` file with the following content:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:665
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"---\n"
"- hosts: rocky8 <1>\n"
"  become: true <2>\n"
"  become_user: root\n"
"\n"
"  tasks:\n"
"\n"
"    - name: ensure apache is at the latest version\n"
"      dnf: name=httpd,php,php-mysqli state=latest\n"
"\n"
"    - name: ensure httpd is started\n"
"      systemd: name=httpd state=started\n"
"\n"
"    - name: ensure mariadb is at the latest version\n"
"      dnf: name=mariadb-server state=latest\n"
"\n"
"    - name: ensure mariadb is started\n"
"      systemd: name=mariadb state=started\n"
"...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:689
#, no-wrap
msgid "<1> The targeted group or the targeted server must exist in the inventory\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:689
#, no-wrap
msgid "<2> Once connected, the user becomes `root` (via `sudo` by default)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:691
#, no-wrap
msgid "The execution of the playbook is done with the command `ansible-playbook`:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:692
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ ansible-playbook test.yml\n"
"\n"
"PLAY [rocky8] ****************************************************************\n"
"\n"
"TASK [setup] ******************************************************************\n"
"ok: [172.16.1.10]\n"
"ok: [172.16.1.11]\n"
"\n"
"TASK [ensure apache is at the latest version] *********************************\n"
"ok: [172.16.1.10]\n"
"ok: [172.16.1.11]\n"
"\n"
"TASK [ensure httpd is started] ************************************************\n"
"changed: [172.16.1.10]\n"
"changed: [172.16.1.11]\n"
"\n"
"TASK [ensure mariadb is at the latest version] **********************************\n"
"changed: [172.16.1.10]\n"
"changed: [172.16.1.11]\n"
"\n"
"TASK [ensure mariadb is started] ***********************************************\n"
"changed: [172.16.1.10]\n"
"changed: [172.16.1.11]\n"
"\n"
"PLAY RECAP *********************************************************************\n"
"172.16.1.10             : ok=5    changed=3    unreachable=0    failed=0\n"
"172.16.1.11             : ok=5    changed=3    unreachable=0    failed=0\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:723
#, no-wrap
msgid "For more readability, it is recommended to write your playbooks in full yaml format. In the previous example, the arguments are given on the same line as the module, the value of the argument following its name separated by an `=`. Look at the same playbook in full yaml:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:724
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"---\n"
"- hosts: rocky8\n"
"  become: true\n"
"  become_user: root\n"
"\n"
"  tasks:\n"
"\n"
"    - name: ensure apache is at the latest version\n"
"      dnf:\n"
"        name: httpd,php,php-mysqli\n"
"        state: latest\n"
"\n"
"    - name: ensure httpd is started\n"
"      systemd:\n"
"        name: httpd\n"
"        state: started\n"
"\n"
"    - name: ensure mariadb is at the latest version\n"
"      dnf:\n"
"        name: mariadb-server\n"
"        state: latest\n"
"\n"
"    - name: ensure mariadb is started\n"
"      systemd:\n"
"        name: mariadb\n"
"        state: started\n"
"...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:757
#, no-wrap
msgid "    `dnf` is one of the modules that allow you to give it a list as argument.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:760
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Note about collections: Ansible now provides modules in the form of collections.\n"
"Some modules are provided by default within the `ansible.builtin` collection, others must be installed manually via the:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:761
#, no-wrap
msgid "ansible-galaxy collection install [collectionname]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:765
#, no-wrap
msgid "where [collectionname] is the name of the collection (the square brackets here are used to highlight the need to replace this with an actual collection name, and are NOT part of the command).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:767
#, no-wrap
msgid "The previous example should be written like this:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:768
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"---\n"
"- hosts: rocky8\n"
"  become: true\n"
"  become_user: root\n"
"\n"
"  tasks:\n"
"\n"
"    - name: ensure apache is at the latest version\n"
"      ansible.builtin.dnf:\n"
"        name: httpd,php,php-mysqli\n"
"        state: latest\n"
"\n"
"    - name: ensure httpd is started\n"
"      ansible.builtin.systemd:\n"
"        name: httpd\n"
"        state: started\n"
"\n"
"    - name: ensure mariadb is at the latest version\n"
"      ansible.builtin.dnf:\n"
"        name: mariadb-server\n"
"        state: latest\n"
"\n"
"    - name: ensure mariadb is started\n"
"      ansible.builtin.systemd:\n"
"        name: mariadb\n"
"        state: started\n"
"...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:799
#, no-wrap
msgid "A playbook is not limited to one target:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:800
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"---\n"
"- hosts: webservers\n"
"  become: true\n"
"  become_user: root\n"
"\n"
"  tasks:\n"
"\n"
"    - name: ensure apache is at the latest version\n"
"      ansible.builtin.dnf:\n"
"        name: httpd,php,php-mysqli\n"
"        state: latest\n"
"\n"
"    - name: ensure httpd is started\n"
"      ansible.builtin.systemd:\n"
"        name: httpd\n"
"        state: started\n"
"\n"
"- hosts: databases\n"
"  become: true\n"
"  become_user: root\n"
"\n"
"    - name: ensure mariadb is at the latest version\n"
"      ansible.builtin.dnf:\n"
"        name: mariadb-server\n"
"        state: latest\n"
"\n"
"    - name: ensure mariadb is started\n"
"      ansible.builtin.systemd:\n"
"        name: mariadb\n"
"        state: started\n"
"...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/learning_ansible/01-basic.md:835
#, no-wrap
